From a158fe7b0c817eebcf2871fe1306347a376030e8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Bard Liao <yung-chuan.liao@linux.intel.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Apr 2026 14:08:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: SOF: Intel: NVL-S: add platform name
Mime-version: 1.0
Content-type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-transfer-encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: a158fe7b0c817eebcf2871fe1306347a376030e8
Patch-mainline: v7.1-rc1
References: git-fixes

The platform name will be used in the topology name.

Fixes: d3df422f66e8a ("ASoC: SOF: Intel: add initial support for NVL-S")
Signed-off-by: Bard Liao <yung-chuan.liao@linux.intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Péter Ujfalusi <peter.ujfalusi@linux.intel.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20260413060800.3156425-3-yung-chuan.liao@linux.intel.com
Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 sound/soc/sof/intel/nvl.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/sound/soc/sof/intel/nvl.c
+++ b/sound/soc/sof/intel/nvl.c
@@ -73,6 +73,7 @@ const struct sof_intel_dsp_desc nvl_s_ch
 	.power_down_dsp = mtl_power_down_dsp,
 	.disable_interrupts = lnl_dsp_disable_interrupts,
 	.hw_ip_version = SOF_INTEL_ACE_4_0,
+	.platform = "nvl",
 };
 
 MODULE_IMPORT_NS(SND_SOC_SOF_INTEL_MTL);
